{"id": 225012474, "title": "Cyprus boosts energy grid with \u20ac45 million infrastructure projects", "text": "The Electricity Authority of Cyprus (EAC) approved \u20ac45 million for infrastructure projects to bolster the country\u2019s energy network, EAC President George Petrou announced on Tuesday. These projects encompass installing new transmission substations, upgrading existing ones, and deploying large transformers, according to Petrou\u2019s statement to Cyprus News Agency (CNA). The EAC Administrative Board awarded two bids during a four-hour session, each valued at \u20ac25 million and \u20ac20 million respectively. These awards bring the total value of new Transport Department projects approved by EAC in 2024 to \u20ac76 million. Petrou highlighted that key projects involve a new substation at Limassol port and network reinforcements. \u201cOur primary focus is strengthening networks and constructing new substations to integrate Renewable Energy Sources (RES) into the grid,\u201d he emphasised. Furthermore, Petrou announced the Board\u2019s decision to develop a new strategy for CERA\u2019s future, with imminent drafting planned.", "summary": "The Electricity Authority of Cyprus (EAC) approved \u20ac45 million for infrastructure projects to bolster the country&#8217;s energy network, EAC President George Petrou announced on Tuesday. These projects encompass installing new transmission substations, upgrading existing ones, and deploying large transformers, according to Petrou&#8217;s statement to Cyprus News Agency (CNA). The EAC Administrative Board awarded two bids [&#8230;]", "url": "https://in-cyprus.philenews.com/insider/cyprus-boosts-energy-grid-with-e45-million-infrastructure-projects/", "image": "https://in-cyprus.philenews.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/electricity.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:36:09", "author": "newsroom", "authors": ["newsroom"], "language": "en", "source_country": "cy", "sentiment": 0.391}